text: Roy Strandem (born 5 April 1932) is a Norwegian ice hockey player, born in Oslo, Norway. He played for the Norwegian national ice hockey team, and participated at the Winter Olympics in 1952, where the Norwegian team placed 9th. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1932 births Category:Living people Category:Ice hockey players at the 1952 Winter Olympics Category:Norwegian ice hockey players Category:Olympic ice hockey players of Norway Category:Sportspeople from Oslo
